children.subject: Leaving the student answer empty in case someone had a different experience -- I encountered a similar situation for a different reason (hadn't fulfilled all lower div reqs so my upper div techs were actually considered as not fulfilling the semester 2-technical req): I got a temporary hold on registering for classes. My hold was resolved before my Phase 1 as a 1-time exception but from this experience I assume the punishment is that your class registration dates for Fall 2020 will be late (I was told by 1 week).

history.content: Just as the the first thread below says... I asked my coe advisor before, and she said the exact same thing

For EECS majors, we're required to take 2 techs every semester until we satisfy all major requirements. I'm taking two techs, but I messed up because I thought I hadn't satisfied my tech elective credit yet -- so I'm really only taking one technical that counts toward my major.

What is the punishment? Does anyone have experience with this?
history.subject: 2 Technical Requirement
